{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/curl/curl/issues/11135","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/curl/curl","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/curl/curl/issues/11135/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/curl/curl/issues/11135/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/curl/curl/issues/11135/events","html_url":"https://github.com/curl/curl/issues/11135","id":1715277480,"node_id":"I_kwDOAAiu0c5mPQ6o","number":11135,"title":"`Curl_poll` may not ignore EINTR if 0 file descriptors are passed","user":{"login":"pitrou","id":1721820,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3MjE4MjA=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1721820?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/pitrou","html_url":"https://github.com/pitrou","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pitrou/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pitrou/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pitrou/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pitrou/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pitrou/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pitrou/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pitrou/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pitrou/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pitrou/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2023-05-18T09:02:29Z","updated_at":"2023-05-19T14:17:39Z","closed_at":"2023-05-19T14:17:39Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"I encountered this potential issue when trying to investigate a [user report](https://github.com/apache/arrow/issues/35318).\r\n\r\nIn the general case, `Curl_poll` will translate EINTR into a no-error return so that the caller may retry:\r\nhttps://github.com/curl/curl/blob/a9f8fe28481fef7c28d85b4a12a3a35521408eaf/lib/select.c#L312-L318\r\n\r\nHowever, if no valid fds are passed, `Curl_poll` delegates to `Curl_wait_ms` which doesn't try to eliminate EINTR errors:\r\nhttps://github.com/curl/curl/blob/a9f8fe28481fef7c28d85b4a12a3a35521408eaf/lib/select.c#L94-L104\r\n\r\n`Curl_poll` is used from `Curl_multi_wait` where it's not obvious whether a non-zero number of file descriptors is always [found](https://github.com/curl/curl/blob/a9f8fe28481fef7c28d85b4a12a3a35521408eaf/lib/multi.c#L1185-L1207).\r\n\r\nThis might be a red herring, but I suppose it wouldn't hurt fixing `Curl_wait_ms` (and/or `Curl_poll`) in any case.","closed_by":{"login":"bagder","id":177011,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3NzAxMQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/177011?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bagder","html_url":"https://github.com/bagder","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bagder/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bagder/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bagder/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bagder/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bagder/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bagder/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bagder/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bagder/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bagder/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/curl/curl/issues/11135/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/curl/cu